msgid "Release Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:10
# 9183ca91965a4abd8dc48ab840225bd7
msgid "When each new version of |project_name| is released it must adhere to the following stringent quality measures:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:13
# 2268c9876eb645c29b284dcb748961fe
msgid "**Testing:** At least 2/3rds of all lines of code must be successfully exercised by a regression test suite which is distributed alongside the software itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:16
# 3b33bdb2b3ea40a7abd7093e271c8ef7
msgid "**Clarity:** The software complies with the appropriate development standards for the language used, i.e. the coding style guide (http://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008) and has been peer reviewed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:20
# 000b629a02bf4346997532d919e57ac8
msgid "**Disclaimer:** The software includes a clear Disclaimer of Warranty and appropriate Limitation of Liability clause. In this case this is achieved by using the GNU General Public Use v3 License (http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:24
# eb8ab7cae65f4f9eaec7d741905fef69
msgid "**History:** The software is maintained in a source control system which allows full visibility of its history, tracking of issue resolution and potential reversal of past changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:28
# 8bc030465cd84ac7b6822111e76e677e
msgid "**Authenticity:** Source control system codes uniquely identify each individual version of the software making it possible to verify its origin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:31
# 6bde246ef31643d3bcd0ba8fd81b8f37
msgid "After these stringent quality measures have been met there must be signature from the majority of the allocated committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:34
# fa60cbed3e1e4c94bb646c9e788d2622
msgid "For a **Major release** it requires approval and signature from a **majority** of the **PSC**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:35
# d63b77daa0134435b2735a4d75a45437
msgid "For a **Minor release** it requires approval from a **majority** of the **TWG**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:36
# f6ac9423e4c84711bcf056ce4c150c0d
msgid "For a **Point release** it requires only approval from **any** of the **TWG members**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:39
# e76d5c1eab2b44c883c2e1dd9fb27b4b
msgid "**Definition of software release levels for the InaSAFE project**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:41
# f3d064abedd24f619f42fb3a20f10e7a
msgid "InaSAFE is built as and add-on to Quantum Geographical Information System (QGIS) so has adopted the conventions used in QGIS:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:44
# abadf4c6a7df4b8bacf0e4b7b376e3ea
msgid "Major releases are versions that provide significant improvements to the software. A major release may change both the user interface and the underlying programming interface. Major releases are numbered as 1.0.0, 2.0.0, …"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:46
# 69449faff22c45f09d27f44331ac6d10
msgid "Minor releases provide extensions and improvements to the software. They possibly modify the user interface but must maintain compatibility with the existing programming interface. Minor releases are numbered as 1.1.0, 1.2.0, …"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general/governance/release.rst:48
# dfc131ed0b1c4409b521a41e42764a85
msgid "Point releases contain corrections of errors, optimisations and small improvements that maintain compatibility with both the user interface and the programming interface. Point releases are numbered as 1.1.1, 1.1.2, …"
msgstr ""

